brand%20name%20of%20the%20synthetic%20stimulant%20fenethylline%20hydrochloride.%3C%2Fli%3E%20%3Cli%3EMilitant%20groups%20use%20the%20drug%20to%20increase%20%26quot%3Baggressiveness%2C%20alertness%2C%20and%20fearlessness.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fli%3E%20%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3ECaptagon%20pills%20fueled%20Hamas%20militants%20during%20the%20October%207%20terrorist%20attacks%2C%C2%A0%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.mako.co.il%2Fnews-military%2F6361323ddea5a810%2FArticle-8a78e9c58574b81027.htm%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EIsrael's%20Channel%2012%20News%20reported%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20drug%2C%20which%20is%20also%20known%20as%20%26quot%3Bpoor%20man's%20cocaine%2C%26quot%3B%20is%20a%20highly%20addictive%2C%20synthetic%20stimulant%20that%20is%20widely%20consumed%20across%20the%20Middle%20East.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Hebrew-language%20news%20channel%20reported%20that%20pills%20of%20the%20drug%20had%20been%20found%20on%20the%20bodies%20of%20Hamas%20prisoners%20and%20fighters%20killed%20in%20the%20conflict%2C%20suggesting%20that%20they%20had%20taken%20the%20drug%20before%20carrying%20out%20their%20%26quot%3Binhumane%20murders.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20IDF%20told%20Insider%20by%20email%20that%20it%20did%20%26quot%3Bnot%20have%20information%20or%20a%20comment%20on%20this%20subject.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIsraeli%20security%20guards%20in%20the%20southern%20West%20Bank%20stopped%20thousands%20of%20Captagon%20pills%20hidden%20in%20a%20shipment%20of%20refrigerators%20from%20being%20smuggled%20into%20Gaza%20in%20January%2C%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.timesofisrael.com%2Fsecurity-guards-foil-attempt-to-smuggle-islamic-state-drug-from-west-bank-to-gaza%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EThe%20Times%20of%20Israel%3C%2Fa%3E%20reported.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMore%20than%201%2C400%20people%20were%20killed%20in%20Israel%20during%20the%20attacks%20earlier%20this%20month%2C%20while%20over%20200%20people%20were%20also%20taken%20hostage%20by%20Hamas.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EFenethylline%20hydrochloride%20and%20the%20Middle%20East%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ECaptagon%20is%20the%20brand%20name%20of%20the%20drug%20fenethylline%20hydrochloride.%20The%20substance%20was%20created%20in%20the%201960s%20in%20West%20Germany%20to%20help%20treat%20conditions%20such%20as%20attention%20deficit%20disorder%2C%20depression%2C%20and%20narcolepsy.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIts%20highly%20addictive%20nature%20led%20to%20it%20being%20banned%20in%20the%201980s%2C%20but%20a%20clandestine%20trade%20of%20counterfeit%20versions%20of%20the%20pills%20began%20in%20the%20Middle%20East.%20Its%20popularity%20particularly%20blossomed%20in%20Gulf%20states%20like%20Saudi%20Arabia%2C%20Qatar%2C%20and%20the%20United%20Arab%20Emirates.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFollowing%20Israeli%20military%20action%20against%20the%20militant%20group%20Hezbollah%20in%20Lebanon%20in%202006%2C%20production%20of%20Captagon%20increased%20in%20Lebanon%20as%20the%20group%20sought%20to%20build%20up%20its%20depleted%20finances%2C%20and%20production%20became%20rife%20along%20the%20Syrian%20border.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20drug%2C%20a%20mixture%20of%20amphetamine%20and%20theophylline%2C%20often%20cut%20with%20other%20substances%20such%20as%20caffeine%20and%20paracetamol%2C%20became%20particularly%20popular%20with%20fighters%20in%20the%20Syrian%20civil%20war%20and%20with%20Islamic%20State%20(ISIS)%2C%20as%20they%20sought%20to%20stave%20off%20sleep%20and%20remain%20focused.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20the%C2%A0%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.acs.org%2Fmolecule-of-the-week%2Farchive%2Ff%2Ffenethylline-hydrochloride.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EAmerican%20Chemical%20Society%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20militant%20groups%20use%20the%20drug%20to%20increase%20what%20they%20deem%20to%20be%20%26quot%3Bdesirable%20characteristics%26quot%3B%20in%20their%20fighters%2C%20such%20as%20%26quot%3Baggressiveness%2C%20alertness%2C%20and%20fearlessness.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20drug%20has%20since%20become%20a%20%26quot%3Bsignificant%20revenue%20stream%26quot%3B%20for%20Syrian%20President%20Bashar%20Assad's%20regime%2C%20helping%20it%20%26quot%3Bstay%20afloat%20as%20sanctions%20and%20other%20economic%20measures%20are%20squeezing%20it%2C%26quot%3B%20Natalie%20Ecanow%2C%20a%20research%20analyst%20at%20the%20think%20tank%20The%20Foundation%20for%20Defense%20of%20Democracies%20(FDD)%2C%20which%20focuses%20on%20Lebanon%2C%20Jordan%2C%20and%20the%20Levant%2C%20told%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20the%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.gov.uk%2Fgovernment%2Fnews%2Ftackling-the-illicit-drug-trade-fuelling-assads-war-machine%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EUK%20government%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20around%2080%25%20of%20the%20global%20supply%20of%20the%20drug%20is%20produced%20in%20the%20country%2C%20and%20Assad%20%26quot%3Bhas%20been%20able%20to%20leverage%20the%20drug%20trade%26quot%3B%20to%20gain%20concessions%20from%20other%20Arab%20leaders%2C%C2%A0%20Ecanow%20added%20%E2%80%94%20which%20led%20to%20his%20eventual%20welcome%20back%20into%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.aljazeera.com%2Fnews%2F2023%2F5%2F19%2Fassad-gets-warm-welcome-as-syria-welcomed-back-into-arab-league%23%3A~%3Atext%3DAfter%2520more%2520than%2520a%2520decade%2Cback%2520into%2520the%2520Arab%2520League.%5C%22%3EArab%20League%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20Syrian%20regime's%20trafficking%20of%20billions%20of%20dollars'%20worth%20of%20captagon%20has%20helped%20to%20spread%20violence%20across%20the%20region%3B%20Hamas%20terrorists'%20reported%20use%20of%20the%20drug%20only%20adds%20to%20the%20carnage%2C%26quot%3B%20David%20Adesnik%2C%20Senior%20Fellow%20and%20Director%20of%20Research%20at%20the%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.fdd.org%2Fanalysis%2F2023%2F10%2F21%2Fhamas-killers-in-israel-reportedly-fueled-by-captagon%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EFDD%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222637%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22assad%20syria%20bashar%20al-assad%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F653a8c5a356802a56be4c9d9%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221978%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ESyrian%20President%20Bashar%20Assad.%3Cp%3ESANA%20via%20AP%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EA%20key%20link%20to%20Assad's%20regime%20came%20in%202018%2C%20when%20the%20cargo%20ship%20Noka%2C%20sailing%20from%20the%20Syrian%20port%20of%20Latakia%20to%20eastern%20Libya%2C%20was%20raided%20as%20it%20passed%20the%20Greek%20island%20of%20Crete.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20board%2C%20authorities%20discovered%20more%20than%20%24100%20million%20worth%20of%20cannabis%20and%20Captagon%20pills%20that%20had%20been%20hidden%20among%20sawdust%2C%20coffee%2C%20and%20spices.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETwo%20years%20later%2C%20Italian%20police%20seized%20one%20of%20the%20largest%20hauls%20of%20Captagon%20after%20they%20found%2014%20tonnes%20of%20the%20drug%2C%20worth%20around%201%20billion%20euros%2C%20just%20over%20%241%20billion%2C%20at%20the%20port%20of%20Salerno%2C%20near%20Naples%20in%20southern%20Italy.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20the%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.occrp.org%2Fen%2Finvestigations%2Fgreek-captagon-bust-leads-to-a-criminal-gang-and-the-port-at-the-heart-of-syrias-booming-new-drug-trade%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EOrganized%20Crime%20and%20Corruption%20Reporting%20Project%3C%2Fa%3E%20(OCCRP)%2C%20a%20combination%20of%20ship%20tracking%20data%2C%20court%20documents%2C%20company%20data%2C%20and%20information%20from%20authorities%20linked%20many%20of%20these%20Captagon%20hauls%20back%20to%20the%20Mediterranean%20port%20of%20Latakia%2C%20Syria's%20main%20port.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20OCCRP%20describes%20Latakia%20as%20%26quot%3Ban%20impenetrable%20Assad%20fiefdom%2C%26quot%3B%20is%20controlled%20by%20Assad's%20b