i%3EMy%20sister%20and%20I%20inherited%20his%20house%20and%20sold%20it%20to%20put%20deposits%20down%20on%20our%20own%20apartments.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EI%20didn't%20expect%20the%20guilt%20and%20self-consciousness%20that%20came%20with%20inheriting%20significant%20assets.%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3ENo%20one%20tells%20you%20how%20painful%20inheritance%20guilt%20can%20be.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20dad%20died%20in%202015%20when%20I%20was%2033%20and%2C%20at%20that%20point%2C%20had%20been%20working%20for%2010%20years%20in%20PR%20and%20communications%20in%20the%20charity%20sector.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20sister%20and%20I%20inherited%20the%20four-bedroom%20house%20where%20he%20lived%20alone.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe'd%20grown%20up%20in%20a%20more%20modest%2C%20semidetached%2C%20three-bedroom%20house%2C%20but%20Dad%20had%20taken%20on%20overtime%20and%20eventually%20a%20second%20job%20to%20afford%20the%20mortgage%20on%20a%20bigger%20second%20home%20in%201996.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20many%20years%20of%20hard%20work%2C%20he%20paid%20off%20the%20mortgage%20when%20I%20was%20older%20and%20living%20away%20from%20home.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20died%20suddenly%20at%2063.%20He%20was%20still%20working%20as%20a%20nightclub%20bouncer%20when%20he%20passed.%20We%20knew%20we'd%20inherit%20the%20house%20and%20his%20possessions%3B%20he'd%20told%20us%20we%20were%20the%20only%20people%20in%20his%20will.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EMy%20sister%20and%20I%20were%20catapulted%20into%20shock%2C%20grief%2C%20and%20a%20bureaucratic%20nightmare%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EI%20was%20living%20in%20Australia%20when%20we%20got%20the%20news.%20My%20sister%20was%20in%20the%20UK%2C%20where%20we%20grew%20up.%20I%20managed%20to%20get%20my%20employer%20to%20agree%20to%20give%20me%20a%20couple%20of%20weeks%20off%20to%20fly%20back.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20someone%20dies%20unexpectedly%2C%20their%20affairs%20are%20often%20not%20in%20order.%20My%20sister%20and%20I%20were%20suddenly%20responsible%20for%20a%20bewilderingly%20long%20list%20of%20administrative%20tasks.%20We%20had%20to%20navigate%20these%20logistics%20while%20dealing%20with%20waves%20of%20grief.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20were%20dozens%20of%20jobs%20to%20do%20before%20we%20could%20consider%20our%20potential%20inheritance%3A%20paying%20and%20settling%20all%20my%20dad's%20bills%2C%20contracts%2C%20and%20taxes%20and%20hiring%20a%20funeral%20director%2C%20a%20secular%20celebrant%2C%20and%20a%20solicitor.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20also%20had%20to%20apply%20for%20a%20death%20certificate%2C%20which%20took%20two%20weeks%20to%20come%20through%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0meanwhile%2C%20everything's%20on%20hold%20until%20you%20have%20that%20document.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EI%20had%20to%20leave%20my%20father's%20wake%20early%20to%20manage%20the%20estate%20administration%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EEveryone%20was%20still%20toasting%20my%20dad%20at%20his%20funeral%20about%20three%20weeks%20after%20he%20died.%20But%20my%20uncle%20and%20I%20had%20to%20get%20to%20the%20solicitor's%20office%20to%20start%20the%20probate%20process.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20uncle%2C%20my%20dad's%20brother%2C%20was%20the%20executor%20of%20his%20estate.%20He%20struggled%20with%20computer%20and%20legal%20literacy%20and%20processing%20his%20own%20grief.%20I%20offered%20to%20help%20guide%20him%20in%20his%20executor%20duties.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20sister%20and%20I%20agreed%20to%20sell%20the%20house%20and%20use%20any%20proceeds%20to%20help%20put%20down%20deposits%20on%20our%20own%20homes.%20We%20then%20had%20to%20hire%20a%20real-estate%20agent.%20Death%20turns%20you%20into%20a%20hiring%20manager.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20had%20two%20weeks%20to%20put%20our%20dad's%20house%20on%20the%20market%2C%20clear%20out%2040%20years%20of%20memories%2C%20and%20decide%20what%20to%20do%20with%20all%20his%20possessions.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EClearing%20out%20and%20valuing%20the%20house%20was%20hellish%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20were%20both%20young%20and%20still%20renting%20small%20flats.%20Confronted%20with%20keeping%20or%20throwing%20away%20a%20lifetime%20worth%20of%20stuff%2C%20we%20had%20to%20get%20rid%20of%20a%20lot%20because%20we%20had%20no%20storage.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWatching%20the%20removal%20van%20take%20everything%20to%20the%20dump%20was%20a%20brutal%20experience.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENo%20one%20told%20us%20that%20everything%20in%20a%20deceased%20person's%20estate%20must%20be%20itemized%20for%20probate%20so%20an%20accurate%20inheritance%20tax%20can%20be%20applied.%20In%20the%20UK%2C%20you%20have%20to%20pay%20a%2040%25%20tax%20on%20inheritances%20worth%20over%20%C2%A3325%2C000%2C%20or%20about%20%24395%2C000.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20contents%20of%20the%20property%2C%20no%20matter%20how%20small%2C%20must%20be%20listed.%20The%20probate%20officer%20asked%20about%20everything%3A%20my%20dad's%20car%2C%20all%20his%20furniture%2C%20even%20his%20kitchen%20utensils.%20It%20was%20hellish.%20We%20then%20had%20to%20hire%20a%20licensed%20surveyor%20to%20value%20the%20house.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20inheritance%20tax%20in%20the%20UK%20feels%20grossly%20unfair%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWhether%20you're%20working%20two%20full-time%20jobs%20to%20make%20ends%20meet%20like%20my%20dad%20or%20a%20multibillionaire%2C%20you%20pay%2040%25%20on%20any%20assets%20over%20the%20%C2%A3325%2C000%20threshold.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20weren't%20some%20aristocratic%20family%20born%20into%20wealth.%20Dad%20had%20worked%20his%20way%20up%20from%20nothing%20through%20working-class%20jobs%20and%20had%20paid%20his%20taxes%20all%20the%20way%20through.%20It%20felt%20unfair.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EIt%20took%20me%20a%20long%20time%20to%20accept%20the%20inheritance%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EI%20was%20almost%20embarrassed%20by%20suddenly%20having%20money.%20It%20seems%20silly%20now%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0I%20should%20feel%20proud%20of%20how%20hard%20my%20dad%20worked%20to%20provide%20for%20us.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20immediately%20put%20all%20the%20money%20into%20buying%20a%20flat%20with%20my%20roommate.%20We'd%20rented%20the%20flat%20together%20and%20the%20owner%20was%20selling.%20It%20felt%20much%20more%20secure%20to%20buy%20with%20a%20friend%20than%20a%20romantic%20partner.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20a%20day-to-day%20level%2C%20my%20cash-in-hand%20spending%20didn't%20change%20much%2C%20but%20I%20felt%20much%20more%20financially%20secure%20for%20the%20future.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhenever%20anyone%20brought%20up%20my%20inheritance%2C%20I%20shut%20them%20down%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EI%20hated%20when%20people%20asked%20about%20it%20or%2C%20worse%2C%20congratulated%20me%20for%20it%3B%20their%20interest%20felt%20intrusive%20and%20their%20praise%20unearned.%20My%20friends%20would%20jokingly%20toast%20me%20%26quot%3Bto%20being%20a%20HOMOwner%26quot%3B%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0a%20pun%20on%20me%20being%20gay.%20But%20my%20usual%20jollity%20felt%20stunted%20by%20grief%2C%20guilt%2C%20and%20the%20complex%20feelings%20I%20was%20struggling%20to%20unpack.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20money%20didn't%20feel%20like%20mine%20and%20neither%2C%20to%20a%20certain%20extent%2C%20did%20the%20flat.%20Over%20time%2C%20it%20has%20felt%20more%20like%20mine.%20We've%20redecorated%20and%20the%20new%20floors%2C%20paint%2C%20and%20carpets%20were%20paid%20for%20by%20money%20I%20had%20earned%2C%20not%20Dad.%20I%20guess%20some%20of%20it%20comes%20down%20to%20pride.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EDad%20was%20still%20working%20when%20he%20died%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20hadn't%20enjoyed%20a%20day%20of%20retirement.%20The%20money%20I%20was%20benefiting%20from%20should've%20been%20for%20him%20to%20enjoy.%20It%20seemed%20contrary%20to%20the%20natural%20order%20of%20things.%20I'd%20give%20it%20all%20back%20for%20him%20to%20enjoy%20even%20just%20a%20month%20of%20his%20retirement.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EInheriting%20half%20of%20my%20dad's%20estate%20also%20sent%20me%20into%20an%20identity%20crisis.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20was%20no%20longer%20the%20working-class%20kid%20pulling%20himself%20up%20by%20his%20bootstraps.%20It%20made%20me%20someone%20else%2C%20someone%20I%20was%20uncomfortable%20with.%20I'd%20spent%20my%20adult%20life%20discussing%20egalitarianism%2C%20social%20mobility%2C%20and%20battling%20inherited%20privilege%20as%20a%20journalist%20in%20social%20and%20political%20affairs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWho%20was%20I%20now%20I%20had%20money%3F%20I%20didn't%20know%20anymore.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20didn't%20dare%20share%20these%20conflicting%20feelings%20with%20anyone%20for%20fear%20of%20sounding%20ungrateful%20or%20insensitive.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI'm%20a%20sharer%2C%20so%20keeping%20this%20to%20myself%20felt%20both%20wise%20and%20isolating.%20I%20wanted%20to%20be%20tactful.%20Now%2C%20the%20money%20left%20over%20after%20my%20mortgage%20and%20flat%20payments%20is%20money%20I've%20earned%20fairly%2C%20but%20I've%20become%20more%20relaxed%20about%20spending%20it%20on%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.insider.com%2Fwhat-gay-cruise-is-like-atlantis-oddysey-of-the-seas-review-2022%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3E%20holidays%20like%20cruises.%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3ENearly%20a%20decade%20later%2C%20I%20see%20things%20differently%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EI%20could've%20blown%20the%20money%20on%20partying%20and%20traveling%20the%20world%20%E2%80%94%20temporary%2C%20hedonistic%20things%20Dad%20wouldn't%20have%20approved%20of.%20His%20legacy%20is%20now%20in%20the%20bricks-and-mortar%20I%20coown%20with%20my%20flatmate.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20father's%20sudden%20death%20did%20teach%20me%20an%20important%20lesson%3A%20I%20should%20work%20hard%2C%20but%20the%20money%20I%20earn%20should%20be%20spent%20on%20things%20I%20enjoy%2C%20given%20my%20dad%20didn't%20get%20enough%20time%20to%20relax%20and%20appreciate%20his%20hard-earned%20wealth.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Finherited-house-inheritance-tax-what-happens-feel-guilty-2023-10%5C%22%3EBu