group-rejects-hindenburg-allegations-in-notice-to-investors%2Farticleshow%2F97405099.cms%5C%22%3Edenied%3C%2Fa%3E%20these%20allegations.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EA%20former%20chairperson%20of%20Competition%20Commission%20of%20India%20(CCI)%20told%20%3Cem%3EIE%20%3C%2Fem%3Ethat%20while%20ports%20may%20be%20considered%20natural%20monopolies%20at%20a%20broad%20level%2C%20there%20are%20issues%20with%20this.%20%E2%80%9CIts%20(APSEZ%E2%80%99s)%20share%20has%20been%20continuously%20growing%20in%20a%20creeping%20fashion.%20It%20is%20definitely%20a%20concern%20if%20there%20is%20a%20creeping%20acquisition%20of%20capacity%20by%20one%20player%20while%20the%20others%20fall%20or%20languish.%20It%20may%20not%20be%20too%20glaring%20now%20but%20down%20the%20line%2C%20say%20in%20five%20to%2010%20years%2C%20it%20could%20be%20a%20problem.%20The%20government%20and%20the%20CCI%20should%20keep%20an%20eye%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20former%20CCI%20head%20told%20%3Cem%3EIE%3C%2Fem%3E%20on%20the%20condition%20of%20anonymity.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fbusiness%2Fadanis-acquisitions-the-inorganic-strategy-behind-the-purchase-of-gangavaram-port%5C%22%3EAdani%E2%80%99s%20Acquisitions%3A%20The%20%E2%80%98Inorganic%20Strategy%E2%80%99%20Behind%20the%20Purchase%20of%20Gangavaram%20Port%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EQuick%20expansion%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThe%20Indian%20Express%3C%2Fem%3E%20reported%20that%20a%20decade%20ago%2C%20in%20FY13%2C%20Adani%20Group%E2%80%99s%20ports%20business%20had%20cargo%20volumes%20of%20around%2091%20million%20tonnes%2C%20accounting%20for%20just%2010%25%20of%20the%20cumulative%20cargo%20volumes%20handled%20by%20all%20ports.%20Over%2023%25%20of%20the%20cargo%20volumes%20were%20handled%20by%20all%20minor%20ports.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIt%20noted%20that%20a%20port%20is%20a%20minor%20port%20if%20it%20is%20not%20government%20controlled.%20The%20nomenclature%20has%20nothing%20to%20do%20with%20the%20size%20of%20the%20port%20or%20cargo%20volumes%20handled.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIt%20said%20that%20the%20Adani-owned%20Mundra%20Port%20%E2%80%93%20which%20is%20a%20minor%20port%20%E2%80%93%20handled%20the%20most%20cargo%20at%20155%20million%20tonnes%20in%20FY23%2C%20more%20than%20any%20of%20the%2012%20Union%20government-owned%20ports.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIn%20FY23%2C%20the%20minor%20ports%20handled%20close%20to%20650%20million%20tonnes%20in%20cargo.%20APSEZ%20handled%20around%20337%20million%20tonnes%20in%20volume%2C%20crossing%20the%20505%20mark%2C%20as%20mentioned%20earlier.%20These%20cargoes%20primarily%20came%20from%20its%20eight%20operational%20minor%20ports%20in%20India%2C%20the%20report%20noted.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EOver%20these%2010%20years%2C%20APSEZ%E2%80%99s%20cargo%20volumes%20were%20higher%20than%20the%20volumes%20handled%20by%20major%20ports%20and%20minor%20ports%20in%20most%20years%2C%20it%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CEven%20in%20FY21%2C%20when%20India%E2%80%99s%20overall%20port%20volumes%2C%20and%20volumes%20at%20major%20and%20minor%20ports%20contracted%20by%20over%204%25%20year-on-year%20due%20to%20the%20pandemic%2C%20APSEZ%E2%80%99s%20volumes%20were%20up%20nearly%2011%25%20over%20the%20previous%20year%2C%E2%80%9D%20it%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CFuelling%20the%20ASPEZ%20expansion%20was%20a%20series%20of%20acquisitions%3A%20Dhamra%20in%20Odisha%3B%20Kattupalli%20in%20Tamil%20Nadu%3B%20Krishnapatnam%20and%20Gangavaram%20in%20Andhra%20Pradesh%3B%20and%20Dighi%20in%20Maharashtra.%20In%20FY23%2C%20APSEZ%E2%80%99s%20non-Mundra%20volumes%20accounted%20for%2054%25%20of%20its%20overall%20port%20cargo%2C%20having%20grown%20at%20a%20CAGR%20of%20around%2036%25%20since%20FY13%2C%E2%80%9D%20it%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EInterestingly%2C%20the%20Adani%20Group%E2%80%99s%20has%20seen%20rapid%20growth%20across%20a%20few%20other%20sectors%20as%20well.%20It%20is%20the%20largest%20private%20sector%20airport%20operator%20in%20India.%20It%20oversees%20eight%20airports.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EFurthermore%2C%20it%20has%20also%20become%20the%20largest%20cement%20manufacturer%20and%20private%20sector%20thermal%20power%20producer%20in%20the%20country.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1698479469000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2016%2F07%2FAdani_Mundra_Port_Kutch_Gujarat1.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fbusiness%2Fin-10-years-total-cargo-handled-by-adani-ports-jumped-nearly-fourfold-to-337-mt-in-fy23-report%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22With%20as%20many%20as%2014%20ports%20and%20terminals%2C%20the%20Adani%20Group%20handles%20a%20quarter%20of%20all%20cargo%20passing%20through%20India%E2%80%99s%20ports%2C%20the%20Indian%20Express%20has%20reported.%20On%20the%20other%20hand%2C%20the%20government's%20share%20has%20dropped%20to%20around%2054.5%25%20from%2058.5%25%20in%202013.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A2%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fbusiness%2Fin-10-years-total-cargo-handled-by-adani-ports-jumped-nearly-fourfold-to-337-mt-in-fy23-report%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Maharashtra%20BJP%20Chief%20Reveals%20Truth%20Behind%20D%20Fadnavis's%20%26quot%3BI'll%20Return%26quot%3B%20Video%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EA%20day%20after%20the%20Maharashtra%20BJP%20posted%20an%20old%20video%20of%20former%20chief%20minister%20Devendra%20Fadnavis%20announcing%20that%20he%20will%20return%20to%20helm%20the%20state%2C%20the%20saffron%20party's%20state%20unit%20president%20Chandrashekhar%20Bawankule%20claimed%20the%20video%20was%20posted%20by%20an%20%26quot%3Benthusiastic%26quot%3B%20party%20worker%20and%20no%20wrong%20interpretation%20should%20be%20drawn%20out%20of%20it.%20Talking%20to%20reporters%20here%20on%20Friday%2C%20Bawankule%20also%20said%20that%20the%20upcoming%20Maharashtra%20elections%20would%20be%20fought%20under%20the%20leadership%20of%20Chief%20Minister%20Eknath%20Shinde.%3C%2Fp