m%2Ficc-cricket-world-cup-2023%2Fdont-fool-people-india-greats-damning-charge-on-drs-after-pakistan-vs-south-africa-cricket-world-cup-game-4522200%2Famp%2F1%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Parliamentary%20Panel%20Defers%20Adopting%20Draft%20Report%20on%20Bills%20to%20Replace%20Criminal%20Laws%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F30123153%2Fimage3-1.jpeg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20The%20Parliamentary%20Standing%20Committee%20on%20Home%20Affairs%20did%20not%20adopt%20the%20draft%20report%20on%20the%20three%20Bills%20that%20seek%20to%20replace%20existing%20criminal%20laws%20on%20Friday%20as%20scheduled%2C%20as%20opposition%20members%20sought%20more%20to%20examine%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thehindu.com%2Fnews%2Fnational%2Fparliamentary-panel-on-home-affairs-withholds-draft-report-on-bills-replacing-criminal-laws%2Farticle67466923.ece%5C%22%3EAccording%20to%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Hindu%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20while%20the%20English%20version%20of%20the%20draft%20report%20was%20circulated%20last%20week%2C%20the%20Hindi%20version%20was%20sent%20to%20the%20panel%E2%80%99s%20members%20only%20on%20Thursday%20evening%2C%20hours%20before%20it%20was%20slated%20to%20be%20adopted.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20newspaper%20reported%20that%20Congress%20MPs%20Adhir%20Ranjan%20Chowdhary%20and%20Digivijay%20Singh%2C%20and%20Dravida%20Munnetra%20Kazhagam%20(DMK)%20MP%20N.R.%20Elango%20have%20filed%20dissent%20notes%20to%20chairman%20Brijlal%2C%20demanding%20changes%20to%20the%20Bharatiya%20Nyaya%20Sanhita%20Bill%2C%202023%20(to%20replace%20the%20Indian%20Penal%20Code)%2C%20and%20the%20Bharatiya%20Nagarik%20Suraksha%20Sanhita%20Bill%2C%202023%20(to%20replace%20the%20Code%20of%20Criminal%20Procedure).%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThere%20is%20%E2%80%9Cunanimity%E2%80%9D%20in%20the%20draft%20report%20regarding%20the%20Bharatiya%20Sakshya%20Bill%2C%202023%20which%20will%20replace%20the%20Indian%20Evidence%20Act%2C%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Hindu%3C%2Fem%3E%20reported.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20Bills%20were%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fsedition-law-repealed-three-new-bills-tabled-in-parliament-to-replace-criminal-laws%5C%22%3Eintroduced%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20August%2C%20during%20the%20Monsoon%20Session%20of%20Parliament%2C%20by%20Union%20home%20minister%20Amit%20Shah%20and%20were%20immediately%20sent%20to%20the%20standing%20committee.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Findia-news%2Fdraft-report-on-bills-to-replace-criminal-laws-not-adopted-meet-on-nov-6-123102700403_1.html%5C%22%3Ereports%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20the%20panel%20is%20scheduled%20to%20meet%20again%20on%20November%206.%20The%20panel%20has%20held%2012%20meetings%20so%20far%20on%20the%20three%20Bills%2C%20which%20opposition%20members%20feel%20is%20inadequate%20given%20the%20changes%20that%20they%20propose.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20Read%20%7C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fknow-the-three-new-criminal-bills-whats-new-and-whats-old%5C%22%3EKnow%20The%20Three%20New%20Criminal%20Bills%3A%20What%E2%80%99s%20New%20and%20What%E2%80%99s%20Old%3F%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAfter%20Friday%E2%80%99s%20meeting%20began%2C%20according%20to%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Hindu%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20panel%20chairman%20Brijlal%2C%20a%20BJP%20MP%2C%20told%20the%20members%20that%20the%20draft%20reports%20would%20be%20withheld%20but%20did%20not%20provide%20the%20reasons%20for%20doing%20so.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20Trinamool%20Congress%2C%20whose%20MPs%20Derek%20O%E2%80%99Brien%20and%20Kakoli%20Ghosh%20Dastidar%20had%20travelled%20to%20Delhi%20for%20the%20meeting%2C%20criticised%20the%20chairman%20for%20not%20providing%20the%20reasons.%20Their%20party%20had%20written%20to%20Brijlal%20on%20Friday%20morning%2C%20saying%20that%20the%20committee%20should%20seek%20an%20extension%20of%20at%20least%20three%20months%20to%20submit%20its%20report%20on%20the%20Bills.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ECongress%20MP%20P.%20Chidambaram%20had%20also%20sought%20more%20time%20and%20increased%20consultations%20on%20the%20Bills.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Hindu%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20DMK%20MP.%20Elango%20raised%20%E2%80%9Cthree%20key%20points%E2%80%9D%20at%20Friday%E2%80%99s%20meeting.%20The%20Bills%20need%20%E2%80%9Cextensive%20consultations%E2%80%9D%20with%20governments%20and%20stakeholders%20in%20the%20states%2C%20he%20said.%20He%20also%20criticised%20the%20Hindi%20nomenclature%20of%20the%20Bills%20for%20being%20%E2%80%9Cexclusionary%20for%20a%20large%20section%20of%20the%20country%E2%80%9D.%20He%20added%20that%20because%20the%20Bills%20are%20%E2%80%9Clargely%20a%20copy%20of%20the%20existing%20codes%E2%80%9D%2C%20the%20government%20could%20have%20sought%20to%20amend%20the%20laws%20instead%20of%20bringing%20in%20new%20legislation%2C%20according%20to%20the%20newspaper.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EEarlier%20reports%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.indiatoday.in%2Findia%2Fstory%2Freinstating-section-377-gender-neutral-adultery-law-parliamentary-panel-criminal-laws-bills-recommendations-changes-2454290-2023-10-27%5C%22%3Esaid%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20the%20draft%20report%20recommends%20that%20a%20gender-neutral%20provision%20criminalising%20adultery%20should%20be%20brought%20in%2C%20as%20well%20as%20criminalising%20non-consensual%20sex%20between%20men%2C%20women%20or%20transpersons.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1698475218000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F30123153%2Fimage3-1.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fparliamentary-panel-defers-adopting-draft-report-criminal-laws%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Three%20opposition%20members%20filed%20dissent%20notes%2C%20demanding%20changes%20to%20the%20Bills%20that%20seek%20to%20replace%20the%20Indian%20Penal%20Code%20and%20the%20Code%20of%20Criminal%20Proce