22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A2%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Fcompanies%2Fnews%2Fril-s-mukesh-ambani-receives-death-threat-email-demands-rs-20-crore-123102800164_1.html%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-business--standard-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Famp%2Fcompanies%2Fnews%2Fril-s-mukesh-ambani-receives-death-threat-email-demands-rs-20-crore-123102800164_1.html%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Famp%2Fcompanies%2Fnews%2Fril-s-mukesh-ambani-receives-death-threat-email-demands-rs-20-crore-123102800164_1.html%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22A%20New%20Treaty%20Can%20Create%20a%20More%20'Human'%20Ocean%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F28110027%2F41233555665_3a98f9f667_c.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EOver%20the%20past%2010%20years%2C%20there%20have%20been%20an%20increasing%20number%20of%20international%20gatherings%2C%20which%20is%20a%20sign%20of%20growing%20interest%20in%20ocean%20governance.%20These%20include%20the%20International%20Marine%20Protected%20Areas%20Congress%2C%20which%20has%20been%20organised%20three%20times%20since%202005%3B%20the%20Global%20Ocean%20Forum%20on%20Oceans%2C%20Coasts%2C%20and%20Islands%2C%20which%20has%20been%20held%20five%20times%20since%202001%3B%20the%20World%20Small-Scale%20Fisheries%20Congress%2C%20which%20has%20been%20held%20twice%2C%20in%202010%20and%202014%3B%20the%20World%20Ocean%20Summit%2C%20which%20has%20been%20held%20three%20times%20since%202010%3B%20and%20the%20Our%20Oceans%20Conference.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThese%20gatherings%20represent%20the%20scientific%2C%20governmental%2C%20nongovernmental%2C%20and%20business%20interests%20concerning%20specific%20maritime%20activities%20and%20ocean%20governance%20more%20generally.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20new%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.un.org%2Fbbnj%2Fsites%2Fwww.un.org.bbnj%2Ffiles%2Fdraft_agreement_advanced_unedited_for_posting_v1.pdf%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3ETreaty%20on%20Biodiversity%20in%20Areas%20Beyond%20National%20Jurisdiction%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20(BBNJ%20Agreement)%20was%20approved%20in%20March%202023%20at%20the%20United%20Nations%20in%20New%20York%2C%20concluding%20nearly%20two%20decades%20of%20negotiations.%20On%20September%2020%2C%202023%2C%20the%20BBNJ%20Agreement%20%E2%80%93%20an%20Agreement%20for%20Implementing%20the%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.imo.org%2Fen%2Fourwork%2Flegal%2Fpages%2Funitednationsconventiononthelawofthesea.aspx%23%3A~%3Atext%3DThe%2520United%2520Nations%2520Convention%2520on%2Cthe%2520oceans%2520and%2520their%2520resources.%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EUN%20Convention%20on%20the%20Law%20of%20the%20Sea%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20or%20UNCLOS%20%E2%80%93%20was%20made%20available%20for%20signature.%20After%20the%2060%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Eth%3C%2Fspan%3E%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fsdg.iisd.org%2Fevents%2Fbbnj-agreement-signing-ceremony%2F%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Einstrument%20of%20ratification%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20has%20been%20deposited%2C%20the%20Agreement%20will%20become%20effective.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EIntegrating%20BBNJ%20with%20public%20international%20law%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAmbitious%20requirements%20in%20the%20BBNJ%20Agreement%E2%80%99s%20four%20major%20components%20%E2%80%93%20Marine%20Genetic%20Resources%20(MGR)%2C%20Area-Based%20Management%20Tools%20(AMT)%2C%20Environmental%20Impact%20Assessment%20and%20Capacity-Building%20(EIACB)%20%E2%80%93%20will%20prompt%20discussions%20of%20novel%20ways%20to%20integrate%20with%20conventional%20public%20international%20law.%20The%20BBNJ%20Agreement%20gives%20the%20governance%20of%20the%20oceans%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcil.nus.edu.sg%2Fblogs%2Fthe-bbnj-agreement-links-between-the-new-and-existing-laws-on-protecting-marine-biodiversity%2F%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Enew%20dimensions%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20that%20reflect%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Frepository.si.edu%2Fbitstream%2Fhandle%2F10088%2F115729%2FSpalding_and_Suman.pdf%3Fsequence%3D1%26isAllowed%3Dy%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Esociological%20and%20political%20changes%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E.%20New%20conceptual%2C%20regulatory%2C%20and%20procedural%20interactions%20under%20and%20through%20UNCLOS%20are%20made%20possible%20by%20this%20agreement.%20One%20of%20these%20breakthroughs%20is%20the%20idea%20of%20marine%20biological%20variety%2C%20which%20can%20potentially%20close%20the%20genetic%20resource%20gap%20between%20marine%20living%20resources%20and%20those%20found%20in%20the%20high%20seas.%20The%20BBNJ%20agreement%20also%20enables%20non-parties%20of%20UNCLOS%20to%20join%20without%20becoming%20a%20party%20to%20UNCLOS.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EConcerning%20activities%20like%20deep%20seabed%20mining%2C%20shipping%2C%20and%20fisheries%2C%20UNCLOS%20chose%20a%20sector%20management%20and%20species-based%20approach%20in%20the%20Marine%20Areas%20Beyond%20National%20Jurisdiction%20or%20ABNJ%2C%20splitting%20them%20into%20separate%20and%20(often)%20isolated%20legal%20frameworks.%20As%20a%20result%2C%20these%20%E2%80%9Cfractions%E2%80%9D%20in%20the%20legal%20system%20made%20it%20more%20challenging%20for%20the%20general%20public%20to%20join%20the%20legislative%20and%20executive%20decision-making%20processes%20in%20the%20ABNJ.%20Adopting%20a%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fbrill.com%2Fview%2Fjournals%2Focyo%2F33%2F1%2Farticle-p1_1.xml%3Flanguage%3Den%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Escience-based%20approach%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20to%20protected%20areas%2C%20impact%20assessment%20requirements%2C%20and%20more%20equitable%20access%20to%20genetic%20resources%20and%20benefit-sharing%20are%20among%20the%20demands%20of%20indigenous%20peoples%2C%20local%20communities%2C%20and%20civil%20society.%20The%20instant%20post%20focuses%20on%20two%20primary%20regime%20interactions%20in%20the%20BBNJ%20Agreement%3A%20a)%20communications%20among%20international%20organisations%20and%20b)%20non-state%20actors.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3ECommunications%20among%20international%20organisations%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20contemporary%20empirical%20research%20indicates%20that%20more%20than%2052%20international%20organisations%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fpdf.sciencedirectassets.com%2F311593%2F1-s2.0-S2352340923X00031%2F1-s2.0-S235234092300272X%2Fmain.pdf%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3E%C2%A0are%20involved%20in%20various%20BBNJ%20Agreement%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20components%2C%20and%20during%20the%20five%20Intergovernmental%20Conferences%20between%202018%20and%202022%2C%20nations%20referenced%2038%20international%20organisations%20in%2039%20clauses.%20The%20BBNJ%20Agreement%20suggests%20standardising%20processes%20at%20the%20global%20level%20as%20one%20method%20to%20alter%20relationships.%20Article%2023%20on%20Environmental%20Impact%20Assessments%20serves%20as%20an%20illustration%20of%20an%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.sciencedirect.com%2Fscience%2Farticle%2Fpii%2FS0195925521000044%3Fvia%253Dihub%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Einternationalisation%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20strategy.%20The%20%E2%80%98clearing-house%20mechanism%E2%80%99%20inside%20the%20institutional%20framework%20of%20the%20BBNJ%20is%20where%20proceedings%20are%20directed%20in%20extraordinary%20instances%20when%20there%20are%20no%20monitoring%20or%20review%20mechanisms%20from%20other%20governing%20institutions.%20An%20analogous%20example%20is%20Article%2022%20(2)%2C%20which%20mandates%20states%20conducting%20activities%20within%20their%20national%20borders%20that%20%E2%80%9Cmay%20cause%20substantial%20pollution%20of%20or%20significant%20and%20harmful%20changes%20to%20the%20marine%20environment%20in%20ABNJ%E2%80%9D%20to%20comply%20with%20several%20BBNJ%20Agreement%20procedural%20requirements%2C%20such%20as%20disclosing%20any%20pertinent%20information%2C%20monitoring%2C%20and%20publishing%20monitoring%20reports.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20next%20question%20is%20how%20the%20institutional%20framework%20of%20BBNJ%20will%20interact%20with%20other%20organisations%20that%20already%20apply%20their%20standards%20for%20Marine%20Protected%20Areas%20or%20Environmental%20Impact%20Assessments%20in%20ABNJ%2C%20including%20regional%20organisations%20like%20the%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ospar.org%2Fwork-areas%2Fbdc%2Fmarine-protected-areas%2Fmpas-in-areas-beyond-national-jurisdiction%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EConvention%20for%20the%20Protection%20of%20the%20Marine%20Environment%20of%20the%20North-Atlantic%20East%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20(OSPAR)%2C%20which%20has%2013%20approved%20Marine%20Protected%20Areas%20in%20ABNJ.%20Large%20portions%20in%20the%20Wider%20Atlantic%20(%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ospar.org%2Fconvention%2Fthe-north-east-atlantic%2Fv%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EOSPAR%20Region%20V%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E)%20and%20the%20Arctic%20Waters%20(%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ospar.org%2Fconvention%2Fthe-north-east-atlantic%2Fi%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EOSPAR%20Region%20I%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E)%20that%20are%20outside%20of%20national%20Exclusive%20Economic%20Zones%20(EEZs)%20are%20included%20in%20the%20OSPAR%20maritime%20area.%20Regarding%20the%20OSPAR%20marine%20area%2C%20this%20Area%20Beyond%20National%20Jurisdiction%20(ABNJ)%20accounts%20for%20almost%2040%25%20of%20the%20whole.%20To%20create%20an%20ecologically%20cohesive%20and%20well-managed%20network%20of%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ospar.org%2Fwork-areas%2Fbdc%2Fmarine-protected-areas%2Fmpa-webtool%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EMPAs%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20OSPAR%20has%20agreed%20to%20designate%20Marine%20Protected%20Areas%20(MPA)%20in%20ABNJ.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20BBNJ%20Agreement%20uses%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.mdpi.com%2F2071-1050%2F15%2F12%2F9461%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Erules%20of%20reference%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20such%20as%20the%20clause%20in%20Article%204%20that%20states%20a%20duty%20%E2%80%9Cnot%20to%20undermine%E2%80%9D%20to%20take%20a%20comprehensive%20approach%20to%20some%20procedural%20and%20substantive%20obligations%20while%20simultaneously%20acknowledging%20regional%20and%20institutional%20competence%20limitations.%20There%20is%20ongoing%20scholarly%20discussion%20about%20whether%20the%20BBNJ%20Agreement%20adopts%20a%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.sciencedirect.com%2Fscience%2Farticle%2Fabs%2Fpii%2FS0308597X19308796%3Fvia%253Dihub%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Eregional%2C%20hybrid%2C%20or%20global%20approach%20to%20ocean%20governance%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20and%20supports%20a%20comprehensive%20approach%20to%20the%20package%E2%80%99s%20four%20components%20and%20a%20robust%20institutional%20framework.%20It%20is%20uncertain%20what%20the%20commitment%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwatermark.silverchair.com%2Ffsx209.pdf%3Ftoken%3DAQECAHi208BE49Ooan9kkhW_Ercy7Dm3ZL_9Cf3qfKAc485ysgAAA1YwggNSBgkqhkiG9w0BBwagggNDMIIDPwIBADCCAzgGCSqGSIb3DQEHATAeBglghkgBZQMEAS4wEQQMELAwu6k1m391hgR5AgEQgIIDCUvAHPH8t1x-3Ml23FzaeOzolMFdC3EKIEdBUfhqYJkuyglLMox81doxjMqqK9VaYFjpu98bBAERs9wMSZFwylvmYq5ZLydRNqNhMHyJnf0MylROrL04Y-BP3xioY_wfKQPusZiSU5bflHs93KGFfzr2Cv4AtvaJHYoYFr6kWROy-OwKDnj0pRsz-n3dvMvvxCrjqbFjSxQAq5YDBNHZDUQAqxwQwCm-RfVmqXnexZPmKPnCKGG6i-CjByNK5AFb-qfBC6fjBtHNJP-tMZ-YDE_h_M_QikW7zyI9t5D51-f54sDfDuO2u4jIx_8HkS5qPFokJOIZ4NIS4-dqG-UigOwsrEkAiSot-b2z2H5tn-3gXZJY9wQZo6vXydP-0yiySIqpOK-HoHFSb7H7-5cfQykp8DiHxZQ8mNzFsY8YPoGnp3YwlXWldzs_7FBtyty50Odwrdxs4BDaLVpiMCY7NTOlrR2kRuj70sILkhnvgwmOVK_wzu47pu7uYVBWyOvyQDSkhTSSNolx82NyuUCOgTs7QGho3FMTJQ2nGqaNYkK9EkksEmlrPedlnpPbEoIM9daYMoJJ3yLdYwGRq5