C%20the%20BBNJ%20Secretariat%20may%20benefit%20from%20past%20cross-regime%20interactions%20between%20the%20Convention%20on%20International%20Trade%20in%20Endangered%20Species%20(CITES)%20and%20other%20conventions%20such%20as%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcites.org%2Fsites%2Fdefault%2Ffiles%2Fdocument%2FE-Res-09-24-R17.pdf%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3ERes%20Conf.%209.24%20and%20Rev.%20CoP17%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20relating%20to%20biodiversity%20to%20impose%20trade%20restrictions%20regarding%20vulnerable%20or%20endangered%20species.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIt%20will%20be%20necessary%20to%20reconcile%20the%20BBNJ%20Agreement%20with%20other%20treaties%2C%20particularly%20those%20where%20not%20all%20state%20parties%20overlap%20%E2%80%93%20it%20may%20be%20worthwhile%20to%20note%20Article%204(2)%2C(3)%20%E2%80%93%20to%20promote%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fpubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov%2F37180876%2F%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Ecross-regime%20cooperation%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20in%20its%20implementation.%20The%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fenb.iisd.org%2Finternational-seabed-authority-isa-council-28-2%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EInternational%20Seabed%20Authority%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20(ISA)%2C%20which%20has%20been%20identified%20as%20having%20a%20high%20potential%20for%20institutional%20overlap%20with%20the%20BBNJ%20Agreement%2C%20is%20currently%20exhibiting%20this%20to%20some%20level.%20Member%20states%20regularly%20referred%20to%20the%20%E2%80%9CBBNJ%20Agreement%E2%80%9D%20or%20the%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.un.org%2Fen%2Fstory%2F2023%2F06%2F1137857%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EHigh%20Seas%20Treaty%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20when%20negotiating%20the%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ejiltalk.org%2Fhow-could-the-bbnj-agreement-affect-the-international-seabed-authoritys-mining-code%2F%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EISA%20Mining%20Code%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20during%20the%20most%20recent%20ISA%20meeting%20in%20July%202023%20in%20Kingston%2C%20noting%20their%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ejiltalk.org%2Fdevelopment-marine-biodiversity-and-the-common-heritage-of-mankind-the-isas-deep-seabed-mining-quandary-and-complying-with-the-high-seas-bbnj-convention%2F%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Epossible%20overlaps%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E.%20According%20to%20Article%20157%20of%20the%20UNCLOS%2C%20the%20ISA%E2%80%99s%20authority%20is%20limited%20to%20the%20mineral%20resources%20in%20the%20Area%3B%20it%20has%20no%20authority%20over%20the%20deep%20seabed%E2%80%99s%20living%20or%20genetic%20resources.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3ECommunications%20among%20non-state%20actors%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.un.org%2Fbbnj%2F%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EBBNJ%20Agreement%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20seeks%20to%20alter%20how%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.sciencedirect.com%2Fscience%2Farticle%2Fabs%2Fpii%2FS0308597X17300787%3Fvia%253Dihub%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Enon-state%20actors%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20engage%20with%20one%20another%20in%20international%20law%20by%20involving%20them%20in%20decision-making%20and%20giving%20them%20institutional%20advisory%20roles.%20Non-state%20actors%20were%20instrumental%20in%20crafting%20many%20clauses%20on%20preserving%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.sciencedirect.com%2Ftopics%2Fsocial-sciences%2Fun-general-assembly%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Emarine%20biodiversity%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20throughout%20the%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Foceans-and-fisheries.ec.europa.eu%2Fnews%2Fhistoric-achievement-treaty-high-seas-adopted-2023-06-19_en%23%3A~%3Atext%3DThe%2520BBNJ%2520Treaty%2520sets%2520up%2Cwhich%2520was%2520agreed%2520in%2520December%2520.%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EBBNJ%20Agreement%20discussions%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20which%20is%20reflected%20in%20the%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.un.org%2Fbbnj%2Fsites%2Fwww.un.org.bbnj%2Ffiles%2Fdraft_agreement_advanced_unedited_for_posting_v1.pdf%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Efinal%20draft%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20of%20the%20treaty%20text.%20For%20instance%2C%20the%20phrase%20%E2%80%9Ccivil%20society%E2%80%9D%20is%20used%20seven%20times%20throughout%20the%20treaty%2C%2033%20times%20when%20referring%20to%20indigenous%20peoples%2C%20seven%20times%20when%20referring%20to%20the%20corporate%20sector%20or%20other%20groups%2C%20and%2031%20times%20when%20referring%20to%20local%20communities.%20Native%20Americans%20and%20local%20communities%20are%20mentioned%20in%20Articles%205%20(i)%20and%2010%20bis%2C%20which%20deal%20with%20using%20pertinent%20traditional%20knowledge%20connected%20to%20marine%20genetic%20resources%20in%20locations%20outside%20of%20national%20authority%20for%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fclimatechampions.unfccc.int%2Fwhy-the-high-seas-treaty-is-a-breakthrough-for-the-ocean-and-the-planet%2F%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Eglobal%20ocean%20governance%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E.%20The%20latter%20also%20recognises%20the%20right%20to%20free%2C%20prior%2C%20and%20informed%20Agreement%20or%20permission%20of%20indigenous%20and%20local%20populations%20in%20decision-making%20processes%20involving%20marine%20genetic%20resources.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EArticle%2011%20on%20the%20fair%20and%20equitable%20sharing%20of%20benefits%2C%20which%20recognises%20the%20significance%20of%20technological%20and%20scientific%20cooperation%20with%20developing%20nations%2C%20welcomes%20collaboration%20with%20scientists%20and%20scientific%20institutes.%20The%20establishment%20of%20a%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nature.com%2Farticles%2Fs44183-022-00006-2%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EScientific%20and%20Technical%20Body%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20(STB)%20also%20includes%20a%20proposal%20to%20improve%20scientific%20cooperation%20and%20to%20directly%20consult%20with%20scientists%20and%20other%20experts%20as%20necessary%20(Article%2049%20(3)).%20For%20a%20variety%20of%20tasks%2C%20such%20as%20%E2%80%9Cto%20conduct%20and%20evaluate%20screenings%20and%20environmental%20impact%20assessments%20for%20a%20planned%20activity%20under%20their%20jurisdiction%20or%20control%2C%20(Art.%2030%20(3)).%E2%80%9D%20The%20STB%20will%20assemble%20a%20permanent%20%E2%80%9Croster%E2%80%9D%20of%20specialists.%20Article%2049%20(2)%20specifies%20the%20requirement%20to%20consider%20interdisciplinary%20expertise%2C%20including%20local%20community%20and%20Indigenous%20Peoples%E2%80%99%20traditional%20knowledge%2C%20gender%20equality%2C%20and%20fair%20geographic%20representation.%20The%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ipcc.ch%2Fabout%2Fstructure%2F%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EIntergovernmental%20Panel%20on%20Climate%20Change%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20(IPCC)%20is%20a%20new%20scientific%20body%20that%20may%20be%20assigned%20to%20the%20BBNJ%20institutional%20structure.%20It%20is%20also%20unknown%20how%20this%20group%20of%20experts%20will%20work%20with%20the%20BBNJ%20Secretariat%20and%20other%20institutional%20bodies%20as%20a%20decision-making%20or%20advisory%20body.%20According%20to%20this%20Part%E2%80%99s%20Article%2017%20(Civil%20Society%2C%20Scientific%20Community%2C%20Private%20Sector%2C%20Indigenous%20Peoples%2C%20and%20Local%20Communities)%2C%20proposals%20for%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.sciencedirect.com%2Fscience%2Farticle%2Fabs%2Fpii%2FS0959652621040804%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EArea-Based%20Management%20Tools%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20such%20as%20Marine%20Protected%20Areas%2C%20will%20be%20subject%20to%20comment.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EStates%20continue%20to%20be%20the%20masters%20of%20this%20ship%20under%20this%20historic%20treaty%2C%20which%20is%20based%20on%20their%20permission.%20However%2C%20non-state%20actors%20who%20may%20actively%20contribute%20to%20protecting%20and%20conserving%20marine%20biodiversity%20must%20share%20the%20helm%20with%20governments%20to%20realise%20the%20BBNJ%20Agreement%E2%80%99s%20goals%20and%20objectives.%20The%20BBNJ%20Agreement%20recognises%20an%20emerging%20trend%20in%20which%20environmental%20treaty%20bodies%20negotiate%20to%20include%20scientific%20inputs%20into%20decision-making%20processes%2C%20taking%20decisions%20per%20emerging%20principles%20and%20international%20law%20approaches%2C%20such%20as%20the%20precautionary%20principle%2C%20and%20making%20interactions%20more%20dynamic%20and%20current%20with%20scientific%20developments.%20It%20promises%20to%20increase%20ocean%20visibility%20and%20cultural%20accessibility%20in%20ABNJ%20to%20create%20a%20%E2%80%9Chuman%20ocean%E2%80%9D%20that%20acknowledges%20long-standing%20traditional%20awareness%20of%20the%20vastness%20of%20the%20global%20ocean%20governance%20system.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3ENafees%20Ahmad%20is%20an%20Associate%20Professor%2C%20Faculty%20of%20Legal%20Studies%2C%20South%20Asian%20University%2C%20New%20Delhi.%20He%20is%20the%20co-author%20of%20the%20book%20%3C%2Fem%3EClimate%20Refugees%20in%20South%20Asia%3A%20Protection%20Under%20International%20Legal%20Standards%20and%20State%20Practices%20in%20South%20Asia%3Cem%3E.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1698471283000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F28110027%2F41233555665_3a98f9f667_c.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fworld%2Focean-governance-bbnj-agreement-marine-areas%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20new%20Treaty%20on%20Biodiversity%20in%20Areas%20Beyond%20National%20Jurisdiction%20was%20approved%20in%20March%202023%20at%20the%20United%20Nations%20in%20New%20York%2C%20concluding%20nearly%20two%20decades%20of%20negotiations.%20Here's%20why%20it%20is%20significant.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthe