C%22400px%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ESettlement%20started%20to%20become%20a%20policy%20of%20the%20Israeli%20government%20in%20earnest%20after%20the%201967%20Six%20Day%20War%2C%20which%20resulted%20in%20the%20Israeli%20seizure%20of%20the%20West%20Bank%20and%20Gaza%20from%20Jordanian%20and%20Egyptian%20control%2C%20respectively.%20Some%20settlements%20are%20small%2C%20with%20less%20than%20100%20people%2C%20while%20others%20have%20grown%20into%20large%20towns%20of%20thousands%20with%20their%20own%20industrial%20areas.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20data%20was%20collected%20from%20a%20number%20of%20sources%2C%20including%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ochaopt.org%2Fdata%5C%22%3EUN%20Office%20for%20the%20Coordination%20of%20Humanitarian%20Affairs%20(OCHA)%3C%2Fa%3E%3B%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fpeacenow.org.il%2Fen%2Fsettlements-watch%2Fisraeli-settlements-at-the-west-bank-the-list%5C%22%3EPeace%20Now%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20an%20Israel-based%20non-governmental%20organisation%20that%20tracks%20settlements%3B%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.btselem.org%2Fmap%5C%22%3EB%E2%80%99Tselem%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20another%20Israeli-based%20organisation%20that%20tracks%20human%20rights%20violations%20allegedly%20committed%20by%20Israel%20in%20the%20Palestinian%20territories.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20legality%20of%20these%20settlements%20is%20a%20source%20of%20much%20debate%2C%20though%20under%20international%20law%20%E2%80%94%20specifically%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.un.org%2Fen%2Fgenocideprevention%2Fdocuments%2Fatrocity-crimes%2FDoc.33_GC-IV-EN.pdf%5C%22%3EArticle%2049%20of%20the%20Fourth%20Geneva%20Convention%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%94%20they%20are%20considered%20illegal.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ETo%20get%20a%20deeper%20picture%20of%20how%20the%20settlements%20have%20encroached%20on%20Palestinian%20land%2C%20we%20need%20to%20rewind%20to%20the%201990s%20and%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fpeacemaker.un.org%2Fsites%2Fpeacemaker.un.org%2Ffiles%2FIL%2520PS_950928_InterimAgreementWestBankGazaStrip%2528OsloII%2529.pdf%5C%22%3EOslo%20Accords%3C%2Fa%3E.%20These%20were%20a%20series%20of%20agreements%20between%20the%20Israeli%20government%20and%20the%20Palestinian%20Liberation%20Organisation%20(PLO)%20that%20sought%20to%20establish%20the%20boundaries%20of%20control%20in%20the%20West%20Bank%20and%20Gaza.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Ciframe%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.theconversation.com%2Finfographics%2F954%2Fa5d24879b7e2bd363807769879e7fac1913f35d8%2Fsite%2Findex.html%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22100%25%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22400px%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fhistory.state.gov%2Fmilestones%2F1993-2000%2Foslo%5C%22%3EOslo%20II%20Accords%3C%2Fa%3E%20divided%20the%20West%20Bank%20into%20parcels%20that%20were%20controlled%20by%20Israel%2C%20the%20Palestinian%20Authority%20or%20a%20joint%20operation.%20Initially%2C%20Oslo%20II%20was%20designed%20to%20provide%20a%20framework%20to%20hand%20over%20territory%20in%20the%20West%20Bank%20and%20Gaza%20to%20the%20government%20of%20an%20eventual%20Palestinian%20state.%20Settlement%20has%20made%20this%20eventuality%20near%20impossible.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20borders%20on%20the%20map%20above%20are%20complex%20and%20are%20close%20to%20overlapping%2C%20leaving%20some%20Palestinian-controlled%20areas%20completely%20cut%20off%20from%20one%20another.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20West%20Bank%20is%20split%20into%20three%20main%20areas%2C%20called%20Area%20A%2C%20Area%20B%20and%20Area%20C.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIn%20Area%20A%2C%20which%20is%20red%20on%20the%20map%2C%20the%20Palestinian%20Authority%20has%20civil%20and%20security%20control.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EArea%20B%2C%20in%20blue%2C%20is%20a%20joint%20control%20zone%2C%20with%20Israel%20maintaining%20security%20and%20the%20Palestinian%20Authority%20looking%20after%20civil%20affairs%20such%20as%20schools%2C%20health%20and%20the%20economy.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EArea%20C%2C%20in%20green%2C%20is%20the%20Israeli-controlled%20sector.%20Israeli%20settlements%20are%20mostly%20built%20in%20these%20areas.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20major%20West%20Bank%20city%20of%20Hebron%20was%20also%20split%20internally%20into%20H1%20and%20H2%2C%20pink%20and%20yellow%20respectively%20on%20the%20map.%20H2%20is%20controlled%20by%20Israel%20and%20H1%20by%20the%20Palestinian%20Authority.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EDisplaced%20people%20and%20conflicts%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EConflicts%20over%20the%20years%20in%20the%20Gaza%20Strip%20have%20forced%20many%20people%20to%20evacuate%20their%20homes.%20Many%20of%20these%20internally%20displaced%20people%20find%20their%20way%20to%20refugee%20camps%20and%20shelters%20run%20by%20various%20organisations.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIsrael%E2%80%99s%202004%20disengagement%20policy%20was%20a%20plan%20to%20remove%20Israeli%20troops%20and%20settlements%20from%20Gaza.%20Prior%20to%20the%20policy%2C%20there%20were%2021%20civilian%20settlements%20in%20Gaza%2C%20with%20around%208%2C500%20Israelis.%20Also%2C%20the%20expansion%20of%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.hrw.org%2Fnews%2F2004%2F10%2F28%2Fisrael-disengagement-will-not-end-gaza-occupation%5C%22%3Ebuffer%20zone%3C%2Fa%3E%20at%20the%20Rafah%20crossing%20(at%20the%20border%20with%20Egypt)%20from%202000%20resulted%20in%20the%20destruction%20of%20a%20third%20of%20the%20refugee%20camp%20there%20and%2016%2C000%20Palestinians%20being%20internally%20displaced.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20chart%20below%20shows%20the%20recent%20build-up%20of%20internally%20displaced%20people%20in%20UN%20Relief%20and%20Works%20Agency-run%20shelters%20in%20Gaza%20during%20October.%20The%20sudden%20increase%20in%20the%20Deir%20al%20Balah%2C%20Rafah%20and%20Khan%20Younis%20areas%2C%20all%20in%20the%20southern%20end%20of%20Gaza%2C%20since%20October%2012%20came%20after%20Israel%20ordered%20residents%20in%20northern%20Gaza%20to%20evacuate%20to%20the%20south.%20Many%20expected%20Egypt%20might%20also%20open%20its%20borders%20at%20Rafah.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Ciframe%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.theconversation.com%2Finfographics%2F956%2Ffd0c2038c556d9563e44b32f6a6905a07c78e824%2Fsite%2Findex.html%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22100%25%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22400px%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ESince%20Hamas%E2%80%99%20attack%20on%20October%207%2C%20which%20started%20the%20recent%20hostilities%2C%20there%20has%20been%20a%20sharp%20increase%20in%20conflict%20events%20within%20Gaza%20and%20the%20West%20Bank.%20The%20map%20below%20shows%20where%20and%20when%20those%20events%20have%20occurred.%20The%20data%20is%20from%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Facleddata.com%2F%5C%22%3EArmed%20Conflict%20Location%20%26amp%3B%20Event%20Data%20Project%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20a%20US-based%20organisation%20that%20collects%20information%20on%20crisis%20events%2C%20including%20violence%20and%20protests.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20volume%20and%20swiftness%20of%20the%20events%20means%20that%20data%20tracking%20is%20a%20few%20days%20behind%20the%20most%20recent%20action.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Ciframe%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.theconversation.com%2Finfographics%2F957%2F382241d83d260b105dc9c40d452cc9f5aaa8b72c%2Fsite%2Findex.html%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22100%25%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22400px%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAnd%20the%20blast%20at%20al-Ahli%20Arab%20Hospital%20on%20October%2018%2C%20which%20killed%20hundreds%20of%20Palestinians%2C%20is%20the%20latest%20in%20an%20upward%20trend%20of%20incidents%20involving%20healthcare%20workers%20in%20Israel%20and%20the%20Palestinian%20territories.%20The%20chart%20below%20tracks%20those%20incidents%20since%202018.%20The%20data%20is%20from%20the%20OCHA%20and%20was%20filtered%20down%20to%20show%20the%20four%20main%20perpetrators.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Ciframe%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.theconversation.com%2Finfographics%2F955%2F3814b3ba2b8c9a60d362848e623da53471993c26%2Fsite%2Findex.html%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22100%25%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22400px