%2C%20while%20only%2014%20countries%2C%20including%20Israel%2C%20the%20United%20States%2C%20Hungary%20and%20five%20Pacific%20island%20states%2C%20voted%20against.%20India%20was%20among%20the%2045%20countries%20%E2%80%93%20most%20from%20the%20Western%20military%20bloc%20%E2%80%93%20that%20chose%20to%20abstain%20in%20the%20vote%20at%20an%20emergency%20session%20of%20the%20UNGA%20in%20New%20York%20on%20Friday%20afternoon.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIndia%20was%20the%20only%20stand%20out%20in%20South%20Asia%2C%20with%20all%20the%20other%20seven%20nations%20voting%20in%20favour%20of%20the%20resolution.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20Jordanian-proposed%20resolution%20called%20for%20a%20humanitarian%20%E2%80%9Ctruce%E2%80%9D%20and%20emphasized%20the%20importance%20of%20adhering%20to%20international%20humanitarian%20law.%20It%20urged%20the%20unconditional%20release%20of%20all%20captive%20civilians%20and%20unhindered%20supply%20of%20essential%20provisions%20to%20Gaza.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIt%20was%20sponsored%20by%20many%20Arab%20and%20Islamic%20countries%2C%20including%20key%20states%20like%20Egypt%2C%20Oman%20and%20UAE.%20Russia%20also%20sponsored%20the%20resolution.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIndia%20was%20also%20among%20those%20countries%20which%20unsuccessfully%20voted%20in%20favour%20of%20a%20West-backed%20draft%20amendment%20that%20sought%20to%20explicitly%20condemn%20Hamas%20by%20name.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20Canadian%20proposed%20amendment%2C%20backed%20by%20the%20United%20States%20and%20the%20West%2C%20sought%20to%20introduce%20language%20specifically%20condemning%20Hamas%20and%20the%20taking%20of%20hostages.%20The%20amendment%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fx.com%2FUN_News_Centre%2Fstatus%2F1717991362010792164%3Fs%3D20%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ereceived%2088%20votes%20in%20favour%2C%2055%20against%2C%20and%2023%20abstentions%3C%2Fa%3E.%20However%2C%20it%20was%20not%20adopted%20because%20it%20did%20not%20secure%20the%20necessary%20two-thirds%20majority%20of%20votes%20from%20the%20members%20%E2%80%98present%20and%20voting%E2%80%99.%20Nations%20who%20abstain%20are%20counted%20as%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.un.org%2Fen%2Fga%2Fabout%2Fropga%2Fpdf%2FA_520_Rev.20.pdf%3F_gl%3D1*w5bv5i*_ga*MTI0Mzk4MjA3LjE2OTY4MzQ0Njc.*_ga_S5EKZKSB78*MTY5ODQzOTgyMi4xMy4xLjE2OTg0NDMxMjYuNTMuMC4w*_ga_TK9BQL5X7Z*MTY5ODQzOTgyMi4xNS4xLjE2OTg0NDE2MzQuMC4wLjA.%23page%3D51%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Enot%20voting%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIndia%20voted%20in%20favour%20of%20the%20Canadian%20amendment%2C%20which%20was%20opposed%20by%20all%20the%20Arab%20nations%2C%20except%20Tunisia.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EIndian%20%E2%80%98explanation%E2%80%99%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fpminewyork.gov.in%2FIndiaatUNGA%3Fid%3DNTA2Mw%2C%2C%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EIn%20its%20%E2%80%98explanation%20of%20vote%E2%80%99%20on%20the%20main%20resolution%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20India%E2%80%99s%20deputy%20permanent%20representative%20to%20the%20UN%20Yojna%20Patel%20noted%20that%20%E2%80%9Ccasualties%20in%20the%20ongoing%20conflict%20in%20Gaza%20are%20a%20telling%2C%20serious%20and%20continuing%20concern.%20Civilians%2C%20especially%20women%20and%20children%20are%20paying%20with%20their%20lives%2C%E2%80%9D%20but%20did%20not%20actually%20say%20why%20India%20had%20abstained.%20She%20said%20that%20India%20is%20%E2%80%9Cdeeply%20concerned%20at%20the%20deteriorating%20security%20situation%20and%20astounding%20loss%20of%20civilian%20lives%20in%20the%20ongoing%20conflict%E2%80%9D%20and%20that%20%E2%80%9Cescalation%20of%20hostilities%20in%20the%20region%20will%20only%20exacerbate%20the%20humanitarian%20crisis%E2%80%9D%20but%20confined%20her%20call%20to%20asking%20%E2%80%9Call%20parties%20to%20display%20the%20utmost%20responsibility.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F28051044%2FF9eI7BYWAAAy7nT.jpeg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F28051044%2FF9eI7BYWAAAy7nT.jpeg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F28051044%2FF9eI7BYWAAAy7nT-300x188.jpeg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F28051044%2FF9eI7BYWAAAy7nT-1024x640.jpeg%201024w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-682182%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22750%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EDetailed%20voting%20chart%20on%20the%20UNGA%20Gaza%20resolution.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cp%3EDespite%20backing%20an%20amendment%20condemning%20Hamas%20by%20name%2C%20India%E2%80%99s%20representative%20chose%20not%20to%20name%20the%20organisation%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20terror%20attacks%20in%20Israel%20on%207%3Csup%3Eth%C2%A0%3C%2Fsup%3EOctober%20were%20shocking%20and%20deserve%20condemnation.%20Our%20thoughts%20are%20also%20with%20those%20taken%20hostages.%20We%20call%20for%20their%20immediate%20and%20unconditional%20release.%20Terrorism%20is%20a%20malignancy%20and%20knows%20no%20borders%2C%20nationality%2C%20or%20race.%20The%20world%20should%20not%20buy%20into%20any%20justification%20of%20terror%20acts.%20Let%20us%20keep%20aside%20differences%2C%20unite%20and%20adopt%20a%20zero-tolerance%20approach%20to%20terrorism.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20emergency%20session%20was%20called%20under%20the%20%E2%80%9CUniting%20for%20Peace%E2%80%9D%20mandate%2C%20allowing%20the%20193-member%20General%20Assembly%20to%20take%20action%20when%20the%20UN%20Security%20Council%20is%20gridlocked%20due%20to%20the%20veto%20power%20exercised%20by%20its%20permanent%20members.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EMounting%20casualties%2C%20deadlock%20in%20Security%20Council%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EOver%20the%20past%20two%20weeks%2C%20the%20United%20States%2C%20China%2C%20and%20Russia%20have%20employed%20their%20veto%20authority%20to%20prevent%20the%20adoption%20of%20any%20resolution%20addressing%20the%20ongoing%20crisis%20in%20West%20Asia.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fworld%2Fus-vetoes-draft-resolution-calling-for-humanitarian-pauses-for-aid-to-gaza%5C%22%3EOn%20October%2018%2C%20the%20United%20States%20vetoed%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fspan%3E%20a%20draft%20resolution%20tabled%20by%20Brazil%20and%20the%20UAE%20in%20the%20Security%20Council%2C%20which%20called%20for%20a%20%E2%80%9Chumanitarian%20pause%E2%80%9D.%20A%20Russian%20draft%20had%20already%20failed%20to%20get%20the%20requisite%20number%20of%20nine%20votes%20to%20be%20adopted.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EA%20similar%20scenario%20unfolded%20a%20week%20later%20on%20Oct%2025%20when%20China%20and%20Russia%20vetoed%20a%20US-led%20draft%20resolution.%20Russia%E2%80%99s%20second%20attempt%20to%20secure%20the%20adoption%20of%20a%20resolution%20also%20fell%20short%20of%20the%20necessary%20votes.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20crisis%20in%20the%20West%20Asian%20region%20escalated%20when%20Hamas%20launched%20an%20incursion%20from%20Gaza%20into%20southern%20Israel%2C%20resulting%20in%20over%201200%20casualties%2C%20including%20hundreds%20of%20civilians.%20Apart%20from%20capturing%20an%20unspecified%20number%20of%20Israeli%20soldiers%2C%20Hamas%20also%20abducted%20more%20than%20220%20Israeli%20and%20foreign%20nationals%20and%20took%20them%20back%20into%20Gaza%20%E2%80%93%20a%20violation%20of%20international%20humantarian%20law.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ESince%20then%2C%20Israel%20has%20been%20conducting%20extensive%20airstrikes%20in%20Gaza%2C%20leading%20to%207%2C326%20casualties%20(as%20of%20October%2027)%2C%20according%20to%20the%20Palestinian%20health%20ministry.%20Israel%20has%20also%20imposed%20a%20blockade%20on%20the%20supply%20of%20food%2C%20fuel%2C%20electricity%2C%20medical%20supplies%20and%20water%2C%20with%20only%20a%20limited%20amount%20of%20food%20and%20medical%20aid%20reaching%20Gaza%20through%20a%20small%20number%20of%20trucks%20allowed%20in%20via%20the%20Rafah%20crossing%20on%20the%20border%20with%20Egypt.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIndia%E2%80%99s%20first%20response%20to%20the%20violence%20came%20in%20the%20form%20of%20a%20tweet%20by%20Prime%20Minister%20Narendra%20Modi%2C%20who%20expressed%20%E2%80%9Csolidarity%E2%80%9D%20with%20Israel%20on%20October%207.%20This%20was%20further%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fdiplomacy%2Fmodi-reiterates-solidarity-phone-call-netanyahu-israel-hamas%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Ereiterated%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20by%20Modi%20in%20a%20phone%20call%20with%20Prime%20Minister%20Benjamin%20Netanyahu%20of%20Israel.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EMore%20than%20a%20week%20later%2C%20he%20spoke%20with%20Palestinian%20President%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fdiplomacy%2Fmodi-palestine-authority-president-mahmoud-abbas-call-israel-gaza%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EMahmoud%20Abbas%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20following%20the%20devastating%20explosion%20at%20the%20Al-Ahli%20Baptist%20Hospital%20in%20Gaza.%20India%20took%20the%20opportunity%20to%20reiterate%20its%20traditional%20support%20for%20the%20Palestinian%20cause%20and%20the%20two-state%20solution.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EMore%20than%20400%20civilians%20were%20killed%2C%20according%20to%20Palestinian%20health%20authorities.%20Israel%20has%20denied%20bombing%20the%20hospital%20but%20the%20video%20evidence%20it%20proffered%20to%20back%20its%20claim%20that%20the%20deadly%20explosion%20at%20Al-Ahli%20was%20the%20result%20of%20a%20misfired%20Palestinian%20rocket%20has%20been%20debunked%20by%20digital%20forensics%20and%20technical%20analysis.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThis%20week%2C%20Modi%20had%20a%20conversation%20with%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fdiplomacy%2Fisrael-hamas-war-modi-speaks-with-jordans-king-abdullah-calls-for-early-resolution-of-crisis%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EJordan%E2%80%99s%20King%20Abdullah%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%20It%20was%20the%20first%20time%20that%20India%20referred%20to%20the%20need%20for%20an%20%E2%80%9Cearly%20solution%E2%80%9D%20to%20the%20humanitarian%20and%20security%20situation.%20India%20is%20one%20of%20the%20largest%20developing%20countries%20that%20has%20not%20called%20for%20a%20%E2%80%9Cceasefire%E2%80%9D%20or%20any%20halt%20to%20hostilities%20in%20the%20volatile%20region.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EJust%20before%20the%20vote%2C%20Jordan%E2%80%99s%20permanent%20representative%20to%20the%20UN%20Mahmoud%20Daifallah%20Hamoud%20described%20Canada%E2%80%99s%20amendment%20to%20the%20draft%20resolution%20that%20addressed%20a%20humanitarian%20situation%2C%20as%20an%20attempt%20to%20perpetrate%20%E2%80%9Cwhitewashing%E2%80%9D%20of%20Israel%E2%80%99s%20atrocities%20against%20the%20Palestinian%20people.%20He%20reminded%20the%20UNGA%20that%20they%20were%20%E2%80%9Cwitnessing%20a%20ground%20invasion%20by%20Israel%20as%20we%20speak%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENaming%20Hamas%20and%20Israel%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ECanadian%20permanent%20representative%20Bob%20Rae%20contended%20that%20naming%20Hamas%20would%20be%20%E2%80%9Cfair%E2%80%9D%20and%20%E2%80%9Cfactual%E2%80%9D%2C%20asserting%20that%20the%20amendment%20%E2%80%9Cnames%20what%20has%20to%20be%20named%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EPakistan%E2%80%99s%20envoy%20Munir%20Akram%20pointed%20out%20that%20the%20Canadian%20amendment%20should%20also%20name%20Israel%20as%20well%20for%20the%20retaliatory%20airstrikes.%20%E2%80%9CIsrael%20needs%20to%20be%20named%20too%2C%20if%20you%20are%20to%20be%20fair%20and%20equitable%20and%20just%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20said.%20Akram%20said%20that%20it%20would%20be%20better%20not%20to%20name%20any%20sides%20in%20a%20resolution%20that%20was%20just%20calling%20attention%20to%20the%20humanitarian%20crisis.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20Israeli%20ambassador%20Gilad%20Erdan%20said%20that%20the%20UN%20hold%20%E2%80%9Cnot%20even%20one%20ounce%20of%20legitimacy%E2%80%9D.%20%E2%80%9CThe%20only%20way%20to%20destroy%20Hamas%20is%20to%20root%20them%20out.%20Why%20are%20you%20not%20holding%20Hamas%20accountable%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20asked.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20Israeli%20envoy%20disputed%20statistics%20about%20casualties%20in%20Gaza%2C%20claiming%20that%20Hamas%20was%20propping%20up%20the%20numbers.%20%E2%80%9CWe%20know%20there%20is%20no%20humanitarian%20crisis%20in%20accordance%20with%20international%20humanitarian%20law%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EWhile%20US%20President%20Joe%20Biden%20has%20also%20questioned%20the%20extent%20of%20civilian%20casualties%20in%20Gaza%2C%20the%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.aljazeera.com%2Fnews%2F2023%2F10%2F27%2Fun-says-gaza-health-ministry-death-tolls-in-previous-wars%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EUN%20has%20vouched%20for%20the%20credibility%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20the%20death%20toll%20the%20Palestinian%20side%20has%20reported%20from%20Gaza%20in%20the%20past.%20On%20Thursday%2C%20the%20Palestinian%20health%20ministry%20in%20Gaza%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nytimes.com%2F2023%2F10%2F26%2Fworld%2Fmiddleeast%2Fgaza-death-toll-israel.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epublished%20the%20names%20and%20details%20of%206%2C747%20Palestinians%20killed%20in%20Gaza%3C%2Fa%3E%20since%20Israeli%20airstrikes%20started%20on%20October%207.%20The%20number%20of%20children%20killed%20was%202%2C655.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EUNGA%20resolution%20condemned%20%E2%80%98terrorism%20and%20indiscriminate%20attacks%E2%80%99%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ETitled%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.un.org%2Funispal%2Fdocument%2Fgeneral-assembly-10ess-draft-resolutioni-l25%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%E2%80%9CProtection%20of%20civilians%20and%20upholding%20legal%20and%20humanitarian%20obligations%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20the%20UNGA%20resolution%20condemned%20%E2%80%9Call%20acts%20of%20violence%20against%20Palestinian%20and%20Israeli%20civilians%20including%20all%20acts%20of%20terrorism%20and%20indiscriminate%20attacks%E2%80%9D%20and%20that%C2%A0all%20parties%20%E2%80%9Cimmediately%20and%20fully%20comply%E2%80%9D%20with%20obligations%20under%20international%20humanitarian%20and%20human%20rights%20laws%2C%20%E2%80%9Cparticularly%20in%20regard%20to%20the%20protection%20of%20civilians%20and%20civilian%20objects.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIt%20also%20urged%20the%20protection%20of%20humanitarian%20personnel%2C%20the%20wounded%2C%20and%20humanitarian%20facilities%20and%20assets%2C%20and%20to%20enable%20and%20facilitate%20humanitarian%20access%20for%20essential%20supplies%20and%20services%20to%20reach%20all%20civilians%20in%20need%20in%20the%20Gaza%20Strip.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EFurthermore%2C%20the%20resolution%20called%20for%20rescinding%20of%20the%20order%20by%20Israel%2C%20%E2%80%9Cthe%20occupying%20Power%E2%80%9D%2C%20for%20Palestinian%20civilians%2C%20UN%20staff%20and%20humanitarian%20workers%20to%20evacuate%20all%20areas%20in%20the%20Gaza%20Strip%20north%20of%20Wadi%20Gaza%20and%20relocate%20to%20the%20south.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E%E2%80%98Release%20all%20civilians%E2%80%99%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20General%20Assembly%20also%20called%20for%20the%20%E2%80%9Cimmediate%20and%20unconditional%20release%E2%80%9D%20of%20all%20civilians%20being%20illegally%20held%20captive%2C%20demanding%20their%20safety%2C%20well-being%20and%20humane%20treatment%20in%20compliance%20with%20international%20law.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIt%20also%20reaffirmed%20that%20a%20%E2%80%9Cjust%20and%20lasting%20solution%E2%80%9D%20to%20the%20Israeli-Palestinian%20conflict%20can%20only%20be%20achieved%20by%20peaceful%20means%2C%20based%20on%20the%20relevant%20UN%20resolutions%20and%20in%20accordance%20with%20international%20law%2C%20and%20on%20the%20basis%2